4:
In other words, sprites exist because
we share the worldview in which
they do. We think, therefore they are.
Uh... I think.
7:
Belief is the first step to altering
reality. Thus, the root of both magic
and sprites is one and the same.
16:
Do you think anything goes as long
as you end your lecture with some
kind of disclaimer?
21:
If the trick is to believe something,
does that mean if we believe hard
enough, we can turn Light into a
human again?
27:
Ooh, I wanna try transforming
Lightsy! It's okay, right Phiria?
32: Huh? I'm not sure if it will work, but...
35:
I suppose we won't know unless we
try!
47:
Get ready, Light! Next stop, Alice's
wonderful world of Humanland!
73:
Oh, my... Perhaps it's best if I step
in—ah, what am I saying? Lady
Phiria can do this on her own!
79:
She may be a teacher now, but she
hasn't changed a bit.
84:
S-sorry... This isn't how it went when I
practiced...
89:
Your lessons are the best, Phiria!
Plus, you're a WAY better teacher
than Sisty!
93:
It's sweet of you to say that, but I'm
afraid my next lecture will be my
last—and so my teaching days will
be over.
97:
Huh? You mean... you don't wanna
be Arum's teacher anymore?
101:
Do you really think I can be... a real
teacher?
107:
You're certainly burning the
midnight oil. Preparing for a lecture?
111:
That's right. Tomorrow is my very
last lesson...
114:
And, um... I've been meaning to ask
everyone. What are your plans after
all of this is over?
119:
Don't expect anything too
ground-breaking from me. I'm still
figuring things out—just like you.
123:
I plan to take some time for
self-reflection. And you, Phiria? Are
you worrying about your path
forward?
128:
Well... I've decided. I want to fight to
protect this place and everyone in it.
136:
But I haven't been able to settle on
what to do besides that.
139:
If I dedicated my life to teaching, I
know that the Academy would
welcome me, but...
143:
You're unsure if that is what you
want.
147:
Yes. Well, no... A part of me wants
that, but...
151:
I just wish I didn't have to decide just
yet.
154:
There's so much left that I don't
understand... So many things I can't
do... I feel like I don't even know
myself yet.
158:
Even as a teacher, I ended up doing
much more learning than I did
teaching... My students felt more like
my friends.
161:
That's when I realized what I truly
wanted to do.
165:
I began to believe that it wasn't too
late.
169:
That's why I... I want to keep studying
at the Academy! To learn all kinds of
wonderful things!
173:
Scholarly pursuits... A fine endeavor,
indeed.
177: I know it's selfish of me, but—
185:
I don't think it selfish at all. You've
done more than your fair share for
us all.
188:
My advice to you hasn't changed.
It's all right to worry, to falter, to have
regrets. We will be by your side
throughout it all.
191:
So, Phiria... Remember this well. The
light you command is yours alone.
As is your future.
195:
I will support you in whatever it is
that you decide, my lady. Because
no matter what happens, I am your
friend.
199: Oh, thank you ever so much!
204:
Hey, Phiria. Do you think you could
teach me about the things you learn
at the Academy, too?
207:
I have plenty of things I want to
share with you, too. I mean... if you
don't mind.
212: Of course, it would be my pleasure!
217:
There's so much we can learn from
one another. That's why...
221:
Ngh... nooo! G-get away from us!
Someone, please—
231:
I won't allow you to harness the light
for such an evil purpose!
236: O light of hope, guide my hand!
241:
I vowed to protect the winds that
blow through Starview Village. And I
will keep my promise...
246:
So that each of us can decide our
own destiny!
251:
O mighty light, O grand wind... I
beseech thee! Weave us a path into
the future!
